

since the inorder traversal for bst is sorted so doing the inorder traversal and storing the elements in the list and returning the element in k-1 element.

global_variable = []

inorder_traversal(root):
    if root != NULL;
        inorder_traversal(root.left)
        global_variable.append(root.element)
        inorder_traversal(root.right)

kth_smallest_node_in_bst(root):
    inorder_traversal(root)

    //since in bst inorder traversal is sorted kth smallest element is k-1 element in the list in the 
    return global_variable[k-1]

    